Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analysing social networks of biographical articles on Wikipedia. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper explores how social connections shape history. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper involves collecting and analysing data from Wikipedia. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques to extract information from Wikipedia. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is relevant as the paper involves studying a digital library (Wikipedia) and its cross-cultural connections.
